item.value: Series I: Roundtable Meetings and Events

p.value: Materials in the collection are arranged entirely as they were received, with the exception of all multimedia items, which were removed to Series IV. All efforts were made to preserve the original arrangement of the materials; the series in the collection and their titles reflect RWF's own arrangement strategy.

The Roundtable for Women in Foodservice, Inc. (RWF) was founded in 1983 in New York City. From its inception, its mission has been to aid the career advancement of  women within all creative, administrative, and entrepreneurial segments of the foodservice industry.

unittitle.value: Series I: Roundtable Meetings and Events

p.value: Materials are arranged chronologically, as received from RWF. Each folder listed contains a number of folders labeled by RWF administrators.

This series contains materials related to public and member events orchestrated by the Roundtable for Women in Foodservice. Regular meetings and panel discussions are addressed in this series, as well as special events and award ceremonies. Yearly calendars are interspersed throughout the series.
This series contains minutes from the Roundtable's board meetings.
Materials are arranged chronologically, as received from RWF. Each folder listed contains a number of folders labeled by RWF administrators.
Note: Contents include historical notes, factsheets, chapter guidelines and by-laws.
This series contains records amassed by the Roundtable. Types of materials include a chapter handbook, local and national newsletters, member directories, and press related to members of the RWF.
Materials are arranged alphabetically by subject, as received from RWF. Each folder listed contains a number of folders labeled by RWF administrators.

Published citations should take the following form:

Identification of item, date (if known); Roundtable for Women in Foodservice Archive; MSS 229; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries.

The materials in the collection relate to the administration and operation of the Roundtable for Women in Foodservice between 1983 and 2001. The collection contains documentation of the Roundtable's public events and board meetings, as well as publications by and about the Roundtable.

Copyright (or related rights to publicity and privacy) for materials in this collection was not transferred to New York University. Permission to use materials must be secured from the copyright holder. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.
